  "concept": "Controlled strain gradients in atomically-thin magnetic materials may generate spatially-varying exchange interactions that stabilize emergent magnetic textures like skyrmions through curvature-induced modifications to local spin Hamiltonians. This mechanically-induced symmetry breaking could enable systematic mapping of topological magnetic phases by exploiting magnetoelastic coupling as a tunable parameter.",
