      "statement": "Two-dimensional magnetic materials exhibit exceptional mechanical resilience, sustaining ultra-high strains up to 10% while maintaining structural integrity due to the absence of dangling bonds. Precise experimental control systems, including four-point bending apparatuses and micro-electromechanical systems, enable strain gradient application with sub-nanometer precision and strain rates from 0.01 s⁻¹ to 1 s⁻¹. Recent studies on highly strained Cr2Ge2Te6 nanostructures demonstrate that mechanical deformation can enhance ferromagnetic coupling and elevate Curie temperatures, supporting the experimental viability of strain-engineered magnetic textures.",
